<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 8:51PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Meagher, west central Judith Basin and southeastern Cascade Counties
through 945 PM MDT...
At 851 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 28
miles south of Belt, or 29 miles north of White Sulphur Springs,
moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Neihart and Monarch.
This includes Highway 89 between mile markers 34 and 54.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
